WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,
obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments
drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line
in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered
the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

13
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!

14
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

15
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

16
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

17
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

18
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

19
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

20
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through

21
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it

22
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

23
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

24
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,

25
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

26
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!

27
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

28
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:53.220
<b>Spin, Pinwheel, Spin</b>

29
00:01:53.510 --> 00:01:54.430
– He won!
– He won!

30
00:01:55.470 --> 00:01:59.430
Arlong Park has fallen!

31
00:02:01.060 --> 00:02:02.600
We did it, Nojiko!

32
00:02:02.060 --> 00:02:02.600
Mr. Gen!

33
00:02:02.980 --> 00:02:06.690
This... This isn't a dream, is it?

34
00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:08.610
I never thought this
day would come...

35
00:02:21.790 --> 00:02:25.420
Way to go, Luffy!
You backed me up perfectly!

36
00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:31.090
Although, as the star of the show, I could've
used a little more time in the spotlight!

37
00:02:31.760 --> 00:02:34.050
Man, talk about a nail-biter...

38
00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:39.510
Next time, wrap it up a bit
quicker, you damn jerk!

39
00:03:08.330 --> 00:03:10.090
This is awesome!

40
00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:25.140
Alright, that's enough of that!

41
00:03:26.270 --> 00:03:27.100
It's him...!

42
00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:30.860
Today's my lucky day!

43
00:03:30.860 --> 00:03:34.740
Well done. I watched the entire fight.

44
00:03:34.740 --> 00:03:39.280
Fluke or not, I never once
imagined the fishmen would lose

45
00:03:39.280 --> 00:03:42.080
to a band of no-name pirates like you.

46
00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:46.620
However, thanks to you, I don't have
to give any money to Arlong,

47
00:03:46.620 --> 00:03:50.960
and all the valuables in
Arlong Park are now mine!

48
00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:52.300
Drop your weapons!

49
00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:55.510
The credit for this incident
now belongs to me,

50
00:03:55.510 --> 00:03:57.430
Captain Nezumi of the Marines' 16th–

51
00:04:00.010 --> 00:04:00.640
Zoro!

52
00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:04.850
We're celebrating our victory.
Don't ruin our fun.

53
00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:15.150
Y-You just try and lay a finger
on me! You'll regret it!

54
00:04:15.150 --> 00:04:16.570
Still running your mouth?

55
00:04:20.280 --> 00:04:22.700
This is for shooting Nojiko...

56
00:04:23.280 --> 00:04:27.620
and for tearing up Bell-mère's
tangerine grove.

57
00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:28.120
Huh?

58
00:04:30.960 --> 00:04:32.210
Captain!

59
00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:39.590
Thanks, Nami! That felt good.

60
00:04:39.590 --> 00:04:42.090
Give him another thousand of those!

61
00:04:48.270 --> 00:04:51.650
You Marines are gonna clean
up after these fishmen now!

62
00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:54.020
And you're gonna help
rebuild the town of Gosa!

63
00:04:54.020 --> 00:04:58.110
And don't even think about touching
any valuables in Arlong Park!

64
00:04:58.110 --> 00:05:00.490
That money belongs to
the island! You hear me?!

65
00:05:00.490 --> 00:05:04.410
Ow! Ow! L-Loud and clear!

66
00:05:04.410 --> 00:05:05.990
And one last thing!

67
00:05:06.450 --> 00:05:08.200
Give me my money back!

68
00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:13.670
I'll give it back! I'll give it back!
It's not worth it anymore...

69
00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:19.510
You're gonna pay, you rotten pirates!

70
00:05:19.510 --> 00:05:22.090
You, with the straw hat!
Your name's Luffy, right?!

71
00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:25.100
I take it you're the captain?!
Mark my words!

72
00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:28.060
Big things are in store for you!
You've made me mad!

73
00:05:28.430 --> 00:05:30.430
It's too late for regrets!

74
00:05:30.430 --> 00:05:34.190
I will have my revenge!
Just you wait and see!

75
00:05:34.190 --> 00:05:36.690
Big things are in store, he says.

76
00:05:36.690 --> 00:05:40.070
How does he know I'm gonna
be King of the Pirates?

77
00:05:40.070 --> 00:05:42.950
That's not what he means, dumbass!

78
00:05:42.950 --> 00:05:46.530
H-Hey, what do we do?! What if
something really does happen?!

79
00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:48.580
Huh?! Huh?! Tell me!

80
00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:53.080
Alright, everyone!
We can't go having all the fun!

81
00:05:53.080 --> 00:05:56.340
Let's tell the whole island
what happened here!

82
00:05:58.670 --> 00:06:00.130
Arlong Park...

83
00:06:00.130 --> 00:06:02.840
Arlong Park has fallen!

84
00:06:04.050 --> 00:06:08.060
You hurting anywhere, Zoro? Here?

85
00:06:05.430 --> 00:06:08.060
Huh? What're you– Hey!

86
00:06:17.190 --> 00:06:19.400
Good for you, Nami.

87
00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:24.740
I can't believe we were
saved by pirates...

88
00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:26.740
Life's full of surprises.

89
00:06:40.630 --> 00:06:43.420
It's over, Bell-mère.

90
00:06:43.420 --> 00:06:46.930
It took eight years,
but we're finally free!

91
00:06:46.930 --> 00:06:48.800
Me, and everyone else...

92
00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:52.890
Really, Nami? You're still here?

93
00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:55.900
Your friends have been
looking for you.

94
00:06:57.900 --> 00:06:59.520
Hey, Nojiko...

95
00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:00.020
Huh?

96
00:07:00.020 --> 00:07:00.860
Mr. Gen...

97
00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:01.480
Hm?

98
00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:03.990
If Bell-mère was still with us,

99
00:07:03.990 --> 00:07:06.950
do you think she'd stop
me from being a pirate?

100
00:07:07.570 --> 00:07:08.950
A pirate?!

101
00:07:09.580 --> 00:07:11.330
Give me a break!

102
00:07:11.330 --> 00:07:14.580
There's no way she'd ever let her
precious daughter be a pirate!

103
00:07:14.580 --> 00:07:16.250
She wouldn't stop you!

104
00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:16.250
Nojiko!

105
00:07:16.250 --> 00:07:17.420
Even if she tried...

106
00:07:18.210 --> 00:07:19.880
would you really listen to her?

107
00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:23.880
Hell no!

108
00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:27.840
I see...

109
00:07:30.510 --> 00:07:31.850
What's so funny, Mr. Gen?

110
00:07:34.810 --> 00:07:38.310
You two are definitely
Bell-mère's kids, alright.

111
00:07:38.310 --> 00:07:39.610
Mr. Gen?

112
00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:40.560
Nami.

113
00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:43.110
You've already made up
your mind, haven't you?

114
00:07:43.110 --> 00:07:44.650
Then live how you want to.

115
00:07:45.400 --> 00:07:47.320
Just like your mother.

116
00:07:53.740 --> 00:07:54.950
He's still at it.

117
00:07:55.870 --> 00:07:58.750
Sounds like Zoro's going through it.

118
00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:00.250
You said it.

119
00:08:00.250 --> 00:08:03.210
It'd normally take two years to heal from those wounds!

120
00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:06.300
You moron!

121
00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:09.260
Trying to treat such
a grave injury on your own...

122
00:08:09.260 --> 00:08:10.430
Oww!

123
00:08:10.430 --> 00:08:13.470
Honestly! Are you folks
really pirates?!

124
00:08:13.470 --> 00:08:14.720
Don't you even have...

125
00:08:15.640 --> 00:08:16.810
a doctor on board?!

126
00:08:16.810 --> 00:08:19.230
A doctor? That'd be nice, too!

127
00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:20.100
Luffy?

128
00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:22.480
But a musician comes
first. Right, Zoro?

129
00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:23.730
Why's that?!

130
00:08:23.730 --> 00:08:25.990
'Cause pirates sing! Duh!

131
00:08:25.990 --> 00:08:28.650
Okay, but why does that come first?!

132
00:08:28.650 --> 00:08:30.660
Hello?! Hello?!

133
00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:34.160
<b>Marine Base (16th Branch)</b>

134
00:08:30.660 --> 00:08:32.530
Yes. This is Marine Headquarters.

135
00:08:32.530 --> 00:08:34.290
HQ?! Is this Marine HQ?!

136
00:08:34.290 --> 00:08:38.830
Hello! This is Captain
Nezumi of the 16th Branch!

137
00:08:38.830 --> 00:08:41.420
Marine code 00733!

138
00:08:41.460 --> 00:08:45.590
<b>Transponder Snail
16th Marine Branch</b>

139
00:08:41.960 --> 00:08:43.290
I have a request for HQ!

140
00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:45.670
No need to shout. I can hear you.

141
00:08:45.670 --> 00:08:53.800
Listen! There's a pirate wearing
a straw hat named Luffy!

142
00:08:49.630 --> 00:08:53.800
<b>Transponder Snail
Marine HQ</b>

143
00:08:53.800 --> 00:09:03.400
I deem him and his four crew
members enemies of the government!

144
00:08:58.350 --> 00:09:02.730
<b>Marine HQ Information Office</b>

145
00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:04.900
"Luffy..."

146
00:09:04.900 --> 00:09:10.280
They took down Arlong Park's supposedly
invincible fishmen, the Arlong Pirates!

147
00:09:10.280 --> 00:09:12.910
Given the threat that they pose,

148
00:09:12.910 --> 00:09:16.410
I've placed a sizable bounty
on the captain, Straw Hat Luffy!

149
00:09:16.410 --> 00:09:18.040
Sending a photograph now!

150
00:09:18.040 --> 00:09:19.120
Roger that.

151
00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:23.830
Huh?!

152
00:09:23.830 --> 00:09:26.590
You couldn't get
a better shot than that?!

153
00:09:26.590 --> 00:09:28.340
No, sir. I'm afraid not...

154
00:09:28.710 --> 00:09:33.300
After a quick verification,
I will submit it for approval.

155
00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:37.970
Don't forget! He's a rotten pirate,
so it's dead or alive!

156
00:09:38.970 --> 00:09:43.520
Put him on wanted posters
across the globe!

157
00:09:56.080 --> 00:09:58.040
Whew, I'm stuffed!

158
00:09:58.410 --> 00:10:01.410
It's nice to just eat for a change.

159
00:10:01.410 --> 00:10:03.290
Are your wounds healed up, Zoro?

160
00:10:03.290 --> 00:10:06.290
Some food and drink'll fix me right up.

161
00:10:06.290 --> 00:10:07.710
That so?

162
00:10:07.710 --> 00:10:11.090
But seriously, how long
is this stupid party gonna last?

163
00:10:11.090 --> 00:10:13.050
This is the third day now!

164
00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:14.390
What's wrong with that?

165
00:10:14.390 --> 00:10:18.010
If you're gonna celebrate,
might as well pull out all the stops.

166
00:10:19.220 --> 00:10:21.850
Hey, Sanji! That melon you just had!

167
00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:23.230
Was there something on it?!

168
00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:25.600
What's with all that meat?!

169
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:29.070
Sure was. It's prosciutto and melon,
so there was dry-cured ham on it.

170
00:10:29.070 --> 00:10:32.150
Ham and melon?! Sounds yummy!
Wh-Where's it at?!

171
00:10:32.150 --> 00:10:32.700
I dunno.

172
00:10:33.320 --> 00:10:38.030
The village is one big buffet party right now.
Couldn't tell you where I got it.

173
00:10:38.700 --> 00:10:40.040
He's long gone.

174
00:10:40.040 --> 00:10:42.370
He's been eating non-stop
for three days!

175
00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:45.370
As for me, that's enough food.

176
00:10:46.170 --> 00:10:47.250
It's about time I...

177
00:10:47.250 --> 00:10:48.920
go charm the ladies!

178
00:10:48.920 --> 00:10:52.920
It is I, Captain Usopp!
The lovable and courageous hero

179
00:10:51.670 --> 00:10:52.920
Way to go, kiddo!

180
00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:54.680
Can I have your autograph?!

181
00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:56.470
who defeated the strongest
fishman leader of all!

182
00:10:57.260 --> 00:11:01.270
Now how about an Usopp anthem?!

183
00:11:01.270 --> 00:11:07.020
♪ Who was it? Who was it? ♪
♪ Who beat the fishman? ♪

184
00:11:05.480 --> 00:11:07.020
What a bore.

185
00:11:07.400 --> 00:11:08.020
What is?

186
00:11:08.020 --> 00:11:10.570
I thought you'd be more
down in the dumps.

187
00:11:10.570 --> 00:11:14.450
Like, "Why couldn't this have
happened before my daddy died?!"

188
00:11:14.860 --> 00:11:15.820
Y'know?

189
00:11:16.780 --> 00:11:19.410
That's how I felt at first.

190
00:11:19.410 --> 00:11:22.330
But now I'm thinking about the future.

191
00:11:22.330 --> 00:11:23.910
The future?

192
00:11:24.410 --> 00:11:27.710
That straw hat guy
and his friends helped us out.

193
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:32.550
But tomorrow, we need
to make a fresh start by ourselves.

194
00:11:33.210 --> 00:11:37.760
There's no way we can forget the
past, and I don't think we need to.

195
00:11:37.760 --> 00:11:41.850
What matters most
is what comes next!

196
00:11:41.850 --> 00:11:44.930
What now? What do we need to do?

197
00:11:45.640 --> 00:11:48.810
From now on, we're the ones
who'll keep our villages going.

198
00:11:49.310 --> 00:11:51.110
That's how I see it, at least.

199
00:11:53.190 --> 00:11:53.940
Smartass!

200
00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:55.190
Ow! Ow! Ow!

201
00:11:55.190 --> 00:11:58.200
Why are you pinching me?!
I don't understand! Why?!

202
00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:00.450
And here I was hoping
to tease you again!

203
00:12:00.450 --> 00:12:04.450
You've teased me plenty,
you inked-up punk!

204
00:12:10.380 --> 00:12:11.750
"Punk" is fine by me!

205
00:12:15.170 --> 00:12:16.170
Will it come off?

206
00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:19.840
I wish I could say it'd be no problem,

207
00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:21.350
but I can't fully remove it.

208
00:12:21.970 --> 00:12:22.720
Yeah.

209
00:12:23.310 --> 00:12:27.310
I know it's stupid of me.
It'll be with me for life.

210
00:12:27.310 --> 00:12:30.100
I don't want anyone to see this!

211
00:12:30.770 --> 00:12:33.900
This... This tattoo...

212
00:12:33.900 --> 00:12:38.110
I don't even want
to be in Arlong's crew,

213
00:12:38.110 --> 00:12:40.570
but it's like I've been branded a pirate!

214
00:12:42.280 --> 00:12:43.580
Nami...

215
00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:48.540
Nojiko! What's that?!

216
00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:49.420
What, this?

217
00:12:50.210 --> 00:12:53.380
It's no big deal!
It's just a bit of art!

218
00:12:53.710 --> 00:12:55.300
Now we're matching!

219
00:13:02.340 --> 00:13:03.600
Say, Doctor...

220
00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:06.680
There is a tattoo that I want.

221
00:13:08.140 --> 00:13:09.060
Here.

222
00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:11.600
Those two sure can dance!

223
00:13:11.600 --> 00:13:15.520
Time for Usopp Anthem No. 185!

224
00:13:20.610 --> 00:13:22.240
Bell-mère...

225
00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:26.490
Your little girls have grown
into tough, honorable women.

226
00:13:27.750 --> 00:13:30.660
It's like you're still here with us.

227
00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:35.130
From here on out, we're gonna
live life to the fullest.

228
00:13:35.630 --> 00:13:39.130
We're only here because of
how much we've sacrificed.

229
00:13:39.130 --> 00:13:44.430
And that's exactly why we're
gonna smile and laugh like idiots!

230
00:13:46.180 --> 00:13:47.930
Ham and melon!

231
00:13:48.270 --> 00:13:52.940
Wha...? There's no food around here.
Aw, crap. Guess I'll head back...

232
00:13:52.940 --> 00:13:53.900
Hold it, boy!

233
00:13:55.190 --> 00:13:58.190
A grave? Did somebody die?

234
00:13:58.190 --> 00:14:00.400
Yeah. A long time ago.

235
00:14:01.030 --> 00:14:05.370
Oh, my deepest conveniences.

236
00:14:05.870 --> 00:14:10.500
Uh... Deepest compliments.
Wait. Deepest concussio–

237
00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:12.750
Deepest condolences.

238
00:14:12.750 --> 00:14:14.460
Yeah, that.

239
00:14:14.460 --> 00:14:15.750
Hey, boy.

240
00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:20.300
Nami is going aboard your ship.
She's going to be a pirate.

241
00:14:20.300 --> 00:14:22.300
It'll be a dangerous journey.

242
00:14:22.300 --> 00:14:24.430
There's no way around that.

243
00:14:24.430 --> 00:14:27.100
I get it. But know this.

244
00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:30.600
If you guys ever do anything
to take away her smile,

245
00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:33.060
I'll kill you myself!

246
00:14:33.060 --> 00:14:36.020
Sure. I'm not gonna do that, though.

247
00:14:36.690 --> 00:14:37.480
Got it?!

248
00:14:39.480 --> 00:14:40.440
I got it!

249
00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:49.490
<b>The Morning of Departure</b>

250
00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:53.580
This the last of it?

251
00:14:53.580 --> 00:14:54.290
Yeah!

252
00:14:54.290 --> 00:14:54.870
Alright!

253
00:14:54.870 --> 00:14:56.130
All done loading?

254
00:14:56.130 --> 00:14:57.000
Yeah!

255
00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:59.880
Right. We've got plenty
of provisions now.

256
00:14:59.880 --> 00:15:01.090
We're good to go.

257
00:15:02.210 --> 00:15:04.260
We were only here a few days,

258
00:15:04.260 --> 00:15:06.590
but we sure made a lot
of memories, huh?

259
00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:08.010
Yup!

260
00:15:14.940 --> 00:15:18.560
We owe you so much for
everything you've done.

261
00:15:18.560 --> 00:15:21.980
We're gonna get back
to bounty hunting again!

262
00:15:21.980 --> 00:15:22.900
We part ways here,

263
00:15:23.610 --> 00:15:26.410
but we look forward to the day
we meet again somewhere!

264
00:15:27.410 --> 00:15:28.370
Take care!

265
00:15:28.990 --> 00:15:30.620
– You guys, too!
– You guys, too!

266
00:15:30.620 --> 00:15:32.830
Well, it's about time
we shove off, too!

267
00:15:34.040 --> 00:15:36.370
Hey, hold on a sec!
What about Nami?!

268
00:15:37.120 --> 00:15:38.540
Maybe she's not coming?

269
00:15:38.540 --> 00:15:40.590
Wh...?! Why not?!

270
00:15:41.090 --> 00:15:44.590
You! You made another
pass at Nami, didn't you?!

271
00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:45.840
Why would I do that?

272
00:15:45.840 --> 00:15:47.590
I know you did!
That reminds me...

273
00:15:47.590 --> 00:15:51.720
She did what she set out to do,
and she has no reason to be a pirate,
You can't stand that Nami
and I are all lovey-dovey!

274
00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:52.720
What're you, stupid?

275
00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:55.100
so maybe she'd be happier here...

276
00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:54.350
What did you say?!

277
00:15:55.100 --> 00:15:56.560
Why can't I be happier?!

278
00:15:57.190 --> 00:16:00.230
If Nami isn't on the ship,

279
00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:03.570
then 98.72% of my reason
for being here is gone!

280
00:16:03.570 --> 00:16:06.570
Hey, you know, I couldn't find
that ham and melon anywhere!

281
00:16:07.070 --> 00:16:08.200
Hey! Where's Nami?

282
00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:11.120
That's the thing! Nobody's
seen her since this morning!

283
00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:11.740
What?!

284
00:16:12.120 --> 00:16:14.040
She's leaving all the money behind?!

285
00:16:14.040 --> 00:16:16.250
The full 100 million berries?!

286
00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:18.540
She's going to travel
without her money?!

287
00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:21.340
But she risked her life to earn it!

288
00:16:21.340 --> 00:16:24.510
She says she'll just steal
some more, so it's all good.

289
00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:28.510
When she says something,
you can't change her mind.

290
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:30.260
That fool!

291
00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:33.970
We're the ones who still have
so much to thank her for!

292
00:16:38.480 --> 00:16:40.400
– Nami!
– Nami!

293
00:16:40.400 --> 00:16:41.770
Nami!

294
00:16:41.770 --> 00:16:43.900
Hey, Nami!

295
00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:43.900
It's Nami!

296
00:16:43.900 --> 00:16:45.230
Get the ship moving!

297
00:16:51.780 --> 00:16:54.160
Huh? She started sprinting!

298
00:16:54.160 --> 00:16:55.410
She said to get moving.

299
00:16:55.410 --> 00:16:55.990
Yeah, but...!

300
00:16:57.450 --> 00:16:58.960
Is she really going to leave

301
00:16:58.960 --> 00:17:02.790
without letting us thank
her or say goodbye?!

302
00:17:02.790 --> 00:17:03.380
No way!

303
00:17:03.710 --> 00:17:05.380
Set the sails!

304
00:17:10.260 --> 00:17:11.760
H-Hey!

305
00:17:11.760 --> 00:17:13.430
They're setting off!

306
00:17:13.430 --> 00:17:16.180
Wait! We haven't thanked you yet!

307
00:17:17.890 --> 00:17:19.140
Stop, Nami!

308
00:17:19.140 --> 00:17:20.600
At least let us thank you!

309
00:17:21.440 --> 00:17:22.350
– Nami!
– Nami! Calm down!

310
00:17:22.350 --> 00:17:26.360
Hold it! I won't let you leave like this!

311
00:17:26.360 --> 00:17:29.610
Hey, you sure it's okay
to let her leave like this?

312
00:17:29.610 --> 00:17:32.320
Why not? It's her decision.

313
00:17:50.550 --> 00:17:51.090
Nami!

314
00:17:59.680 --> 00:18:00.810
What gives?!

315
00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:02.560
Nami!

316
00:18:23.920 --> 00:18:24.460
She didn't!

317
00:18:25.420 --> 00:18:27.210
– What's this...?!
– My wallet's gone!

318
00:18:27.590 --> 00:18:28.550
Mine, too!

319
00:18:28.550 --> 00:18:29.760
Same here!

320
00:18:34.800 --> 00:18:36.390
Take care, everyone!

321
00:18:36.390 --> 00:18:37.180
How...?!

322
00:18:37.180 --> 00:18:41.480
– How dare you?! You rotten brat!
– How dare you?! You rotten brat!

323
00:18:42.430 --> 00:18:45.440
Hey, she hasn't changed a bit.

324
00:18:45.440 --> 00:18:47.270
She might just betray us again...

325
00:18:47.270 --> 00:18:48.980
Nami! Good job!

326
00:18:51.650 --> 00:18:53.280
You lousy cat burglar!

327
00:18:53.280 --> 00:18:54.200
Get back here!

328
00:18:54.200 --> 00:18:55.160
My wallet!

329
00:18:55.160 --> 00:18:56.570
You punk!

330
00:18:56.570 --> 00:18:58.330
Come back anytime!

331
00:18:58.330 --> 00:18:59.450
Take care of yourself!

332
00:18:59.450 --> 00:19:01.200
We appreciate you guys!

333
00:19:02.700 --> 00:19:04.080
Boy!

334
00:19:05.420 --> 00:19:07.920
Don't forget your promise!

335
00:19:11.960 --> 00:19:15.090
So long, everyone!
Until we meet again!

336
00:19:18.350 --> 00:19:20.060
She sure got us!

337
00:19:20.060 --> 00:19:22.850
My little sister's a piece of work!

338
00:19:24.310 --> 00:19:25.560
Have fun out there!

339
00:19:29.560 --> 00:19:31.820
Here, Genzo.

340
00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:34.110
A piece of paper?
What's this, Doctor?

341
00:19:34.700 --> 00:19:39.450
That silly girl. She never learns.
She wanted a new tattoo before leaving.

342
00:19:40.410 --> 00:19:41.790
What's this symbol?

343
00:19:42.240 --> 00:19:45.250
It's a tangerine
and a pinwheel, apparently.

344
00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.920
Oh? Mr. Gen! What happened
to your pinwheel?

345
00:19:54.170 --> 00:19:56.050
I won't be needing it anymore.

346
00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:09.060
Bell-mère, I'm off.

347
00:20:15.610 --> 00:20:18.910
Hold on, Mr. Gen!
Stay away from Nami!

348
00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:22.990
Aw, but I wanna see her smile, too!

349
00:20:22.990 --> 00:20:26.200
She starts crying because
you have such a scary face!

350
00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:28.710
Come on, what am I
supposed to do about that?!

351
00:20:29.330 --> 00:20:29.880
I know!

352
00:20:30.500 --> 00:20:33.800
If I just keep this right here,
it'll make you laugh, won't it?!

353
00:20:33.800 --> 00:20:35.840
Well, Nami?!

354
00:20:35.840 --> 00:20:39.470
Listen, I really don't think a silly ol'
pinwheel is gonna make Nami...

355
00:20:47.390 --> 00:20:49.520
Oh. She's laughing.

356
00:20:55.190 --> 00:20:58.860
The skies are clear
and the winds are fair.

357
00:20:58.860 --> 00:21:02.660
And the pinwheel
spins merrily for another day.

358
00:21:06.890 --> 00:21:11.880
More feelings than I can hold but I can’t make you understand

359
00:21:11.900 --> 00:21:16.740
Be that as it may, I just can’t bear to let go of your hand

360
00:21:16.790 --> 00:21:21.690
I’ve still gotta move, even if I’m alone I’ll walk along

361
00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:26.960
Just promise that you’ll still keep 
an eye on me when I am gone

362
00:21:31.610 --> 00:21:36.490
As soon as I woke up, couldn’t get it off my mind

363
00:21:36.540 --> 00:21:41.240
“Why the hell’s it so hot? I can hardly breathe!”

364
00:21:41.240 --> 00:21:47.750
It’s been quite a while, 
but those thoughts just won’t seem to let go

365
00:21:47.750 --> 00:21:51.630
But hey, what do I know?

366
00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:57.490
Guess I want a taste of that thing people call a “runner’s high”

367
00:21:57.490 --> 00:22:02.370
Think I chased too hard, and ended up leaving myself behind

368
00:22:02.420 --> 00:22:07.350
All I want’s a taste of a dream that a sentence can’t define

369
00:22:07.350 --> 00:22:12.550
Stick right by my side, and I can run, run, run until I die
